entries.femaleVariant: Transmitter's within reach of our mystery van.
There is a transmitter on the roof. Seems to be conveying a signal to a van out front. Know who it might be?
entries.maleVariant: There is a transmitter on the roof. It seems to be conveying a signal to a van out front. You know who it might be?

entries.femaleVariant: I'll wait here. Just don't tell Jeff anything for now, OK?
Found an odd transmitter on the roof.
Sure, whatever. I'll call him once I know something more substantial.
This is way bigger than we thought.
Liz, this is way bigger than we thought. Jeff's entire campaign could be threatened.
Let me worry about the race. Just tell me what you managed to find.
Wonder if Elizabeth has ever seen the car.
We never set up any transmitter. And I don't know a thing about any van, but my guess is it's SSI's.
Don't see any other possibility.
Could be.
Don't really see any other possibility. But we still don't know who they work for.
Uh, could be. Tech they're using seems unconventional, though.
entries.maleVariant: Could be. Tech they're using seems unconventional, though.

entries.femaleVariant: So what do we do with the transmitter?
Nothin' just yet. Lemme check the van first.
Do you plan to check it?
Yeah, about to pay 'em a personal visit.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, about to pay them a personal visit.

entries.femaleVariant: You can always come and talk to me.
Fine, I'll keep that in mind.
That's fine. Just remember it's the busiest time for Jeff right now.
